{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC26"]]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (28 min)","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2026\/269"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC26-269-Whats-new-in-SwiftUI","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Explore the latest additions to SwiftUI and discover how they can improve your apps. We’ll introduce a new Document protocol with direct disk access and snapshot-based diffing for building high-performance apps; new APIs for reordering content in lists, grids, and sections; and toolbar enhancements including visibility priority and auto-minimizing behavior. We’ll also cover expanded presentation APIs — including swipe actions on any view — plus AsyncImage caching improvements and lazy state initialization for Observable types.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc26-269-whats-new-in-swiftui"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC26","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"What’s new in SwiftUI"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Key Takeaways","anchor":"Key-Takeaways","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"🔍 Set any tab to prominent appearance","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"↔️ Customize toolbar placement & overflow","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"🗂️ Reordering & swipe actions for any view","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"📄 Improved document handling"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"🏎️ Many performance improvements","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Presenters","anchor":"Presenters","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Julia Vashchenko, UI Frameworks Engineer"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Steven Peterson, UI Frameworks Engineer","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Refreshed look and feel","anchor":"Refreshed-look-and-feel","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Refined Liquid Glass look will be applied automatically","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".appearsActive"},{"type":"text","text":" environment to conditionally change styles when window is active or inactive (aka in background)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC26-269-appears-active.jpeg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Menu bar items reduce use of icons again ("},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/design\/human-interface-guidelines\/menus#Icons","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":")"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":".labelStyle(.titleAndIcon)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to manually show icon when it makes sense to highlight it","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC26-269-menu-item-icon.jpeg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iPhone apps are now automatically resizable","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check out "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC26-278-Modernize-your-UIKit-app"},{"type":"text","text":" on how to handle mix between SwiftUI and UIKit"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tab(role: .prominent)"},{"text":" to get separated out tab at trailing edge of Tab Bar","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC26-269-Prominent-Tab","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Toolbar Enhancements","anchor":"Toolbar-Enhancements","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"More options to define placement & overflow of toolbar items:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Visibility priority","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC26-269-visibility-priority.jpeg","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":".visibilityPriority(.high)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to lower chance of items moving to overflow menu.","type":"text"}]}]},{"title":"Overflow menu","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC26-269-toolbar-overflow.jpeg","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Group items in "},{"code":"ToolbarOverflowMenu","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" container to "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"always"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" place them in overflow menu."}]}]},{"title":"Pinned trailing placement","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC26-269-toolbar-placement-pinned.jpeg"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToolbarItem(placement: .topBarPinnedTrailing)"},{"type":"text","text":" to place item "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"behind"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" overflow menu."}]}]},{"title":"Minimize when scrolling","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC26-269-toolbar-minimize.jpeg","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".toolbarMinimizeBehavior(.onScrollDown, for: .navigationBar)"},{"text":" to hide toolbars on scroll.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Document-based apps","anchor":"Document-based-apps","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"Document creation context","anchor":"Document-creation-context","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/documentcreationsource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" API to define different sources as starting point:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC26-269-Create-Document-Buttons"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@main","struct Stickers: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        DocumentGroupLaunchScene(\"Create a Sticker Page\") {","            NewDocumentButton(\"New Sticker Page\", source: .blank)","            NewDocumentButton(\"Sticker Page from Photo…\", source: .photo)","        }","        ","        DocumentGroup { document in","            StickerPageDocumentView(document)","        } { configuration, context in","            StickerPageDocument(configuration: configuration, context: context)","        }","    }","}","  ","extension DocumentCreationSource {","    static let blank = Self(id: \"blank\")","    static let photo = Self(id: \"photo\")","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Performance","anchor":"Performance","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Observable"},{"type":"text","text":" macro alone gives performance boost and supports snapshot-based diffing for efficient updates."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/SwiftUI\/WritableDocument"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol to write to documents with snapshot-based optimization:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Observable","final class StickerDocument: WritableDocument {","    ","    static let writableDocumentTypes: [UTType] = [.stickerDocument]","  ","    @MainActor","    func snapshot(contentType: UTType) async throws -> sending PageSnapshot {","        makeSnapshot()","    }","      ","    func writer(configuration: sending WriteConfiguration) -> sending Writer {","        Writer(contentType: configuration.contentType)","    }","}","    ","struct PageSnapshot {","    var background: Image","    var metadata: StickerPlacements","    var stickers: [Image]","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Snapshot"},{"type":"text","text":" notion in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DocumentWriter"},{"type":"text","text":" for further performance improvements:"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["struct Writer<Snapshot>: DocumentWriter {","    typealias Snapshot = PageSnapshot","  ","    let contentType: UTType","    ","    nonisolated func write(","        snapshot: sending PageSnapshot, to destination: URL,","        previous: sending PageSnapshot, progress: consuming Subprogress","    ) async throws {","        \/\/ report progress…","        \/\/ write .stickerDocument","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/readabledocument","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol to read from documents","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Twin to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WritableDocument"}]}]}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC26-269-Document-API","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"First-class support for URL access","anchor":"First-class-support-for-URL-access","type":"heading","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Extend writer to safe document in any different formats like PNG","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add new format type to "},{"code":"writableDocumentTypes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (see above)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conforms(to:)"},{"type":"text","text":" check to handle different"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["struct Writer<Snapshot>: DocumentWriter {","    typealias Snapshot = PageSnapshot","","    let contentType: UTType","","    nonisolated func write(","        snapshot: sending PageSnapshot, to destination: URL, ","        previous: sending PageSnapshot, progress: consuming Subprogress","    ) async throws {","        if contentType.conforms(to: .stickerDocument) {  ","            \/\/ write .stickerDocument","        } else if contentType.conforms(to: .png) {","            let context = CGContext(\/* ... *\/) ","            context.draw(\/* ... *\/)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Presentation and interaction","anchor":"Presentation-and-interaction","type":"heading","level":2},{"text":"Reorderable containers","anchor":"Reorderable-containers","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add support for reordering ","type":"text"},{"code":"List","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or any container like grids via reorderable API:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["LazyVGrid {","    ForEach(stickers) { sticker in","        StickerListItemView(sticker: sticker)","    }","    .reorderable()","}",".reorderContainer(for: Sticker.self) { difference in","    difference.apply(to: &stickers)","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Swipe actions on any view","anchor":"Swipe-actions-on-any-view","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":".swipeActions","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier now also works on any view:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["ScrollView {","    LazyVStack {","        ForEach(stickers) { sticker in","            StickerListItemView(sticker: sticker)","                .swipeActions {","                    DeleteButton(sticker: sticker)","                }","        }","    }","}",".swipeActionsContainer()"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC26-269-swipe-actions.jpeg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Confirmation dialogs with item binding","anchor":"Confirmation-dialogs-with-item-binding","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".confirmationDialog"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".alert"},{"type":"text","text":" now also support item binding like sheets:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC26-269-confirmation-dialog.jpeg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Data flow and performance","anchor":"Data-flow-and-performance","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/asyncimage","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" now uses standard HTTP caching by default","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Customizable via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URLRequest"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URLCache"},{"type":"